[
  "William R. Berkley founded insurance firm W.R. Berkley with only $2,500 in 1967 while he was getting his MBA from Harvard.",
  "His company, which went public in 1974, insures everything from mobile surgery units to jewels to fine art and has operations in 60 countries.",
  "Berkley stepped down from CEO in 2015 but remains chairman; he owns 20% of the company, which generated $8.1 billion in sales in 2020. ",
  "His son, William Robert Berkley Jr., is the current CEO and president."
]